cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.NE, cs.SP

The paper proposes a deep neural network approach for source number detection in array signal processing. This falls under the broad category of machine learning and signal processing, which could be categorized under several sub-categories in arXiv CS. 

- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a deep neural network approach for source number detection, which falls under the category of machine learning. 
- cs.SI (Signal Processing): The paper deals with source number detection in array signal processing, which is a sub-field of signal processing. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper uses eigenvalues of the received signal covariance matrix as input to the neural network, which could be related to information theory. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper proposes a deep neural network approach for source number detection, which falls under the category of neural computing. 
- cs.SP (Speech Processing): Although the paper does not deal with speech processing, the techniques proposed in the paper could be applied to speech processing applications, which falls under the category of signal processing.
